            <section>
                <h1>Salary and income</h1>

                <p>
                    I've talked about money with my colleagues, mentees, and friends for years. Knowing how much people get paid is one of the missing steps to fixing gender-based income inequality (you can also replace gender with race and country of origin).
                </p>

                <p>
                    Last week, <b>Dan Mall</b> blew my mind with his <a href="https://danmall.com/salary-income" target="_blank" rel="noopener">public salary and income page</a>, and just like he borrowed the idea from <b><a href="https://matthewsmith.website/salary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Matthew Smith</a></b>, I also decided to "steal like an artist".
                </p>

                <p>
                    A little bit of extra context before jumping into numbers. 
                </p>

                <p>
                    I skipped over the first few years as a professional working in <b>Portugal</b>.
                </p>

                <p>
                    Like many other Portuguese millennials that started their careers around the <b><time>2008</time> crisis</b>, I spent many years working as a "fake freelancer". Even though I had a boss and hierarchy, workplace, and working hours like any employee, I was being paid like a service provider and had to pay all taxes and social security (while illegal, this is still a common practice).
                </p>

                <p>
                    In <time>2014</time>, I moved to <b>Sweden</b>, where my career took off (or started to happen, depending on how you look at it). All numbers from then on are shown in <b>Swedish Krona</b> (SEK).
                </p>

                <p>
                    Keep in mind that in most European countries, salaries are paid monthly. Just multiply my values by 12 to get yearly figures ðŸ¤“
                </p>

                    <p>
                    All values displayed are income before taxes.
                </p>

